==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Melungeon
<hw>Me*lun"geon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧langer</ets> to mix, <ets>m⟦eacute⟧lange</ets> a
mixture.]</ety> <def>One of a mixed white and Indian people living in
parts of Tennessee and the Carolinas. They are descendants of early
intermixtures of white settlers with natives. In North Carolina the
<col><b>Croatan Indians</b></col>, regarded as descended from
<person>Raleigh's</person> lost colony of Croatan, formerly classed with
negroes, are now legally recognized as distinct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melursus</ent>⟦br⟧
